panels.content:
Summary of a site

We collect data with our javascript agent which gets injected into your pages. This agent captures ajax requests, resource loads and some more information.
This dashboard shows a summary of the most important metrics for your page.

targets.query: SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(none)

panels.content:
Speedindex

This metrics show the average speedindex and the speedindex for the particular browsers.

targets.query: SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE $timeFilter
SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE "browser" = 'Firefox' AND $timeFilter
SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE "browser" = 'Internet Explorer' OR "browser" = 'Edge' AND $timeFilter
SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE "browser" = 'Opera' AND $timeFilter
SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE "browser" = 'Google Chrome' AND $timeFilter

panels.content:
Mobile browsers

Here we can see how well our site is performing on mobile devices.

targets.query: SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE "device" = 'Android' AND "browser" = 'Google Chrome' AND $timeFilter

panels.content:
Speedindex of all browsers compared

This graph shows the speed indices of all browsers. You can compare them easily and detect which values need to improve.

targets.query: SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE $timeFilter AND "device"  =~ /Windows|Linux|Mac/ GROUP BY time($interval), "browser" fill(null)
SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE $timeFilter AND "device"  =~ /Android|iOS/ GROUP BY time($interval), "browser" fill(null)
SELECT mean("speedindex") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE $timeFilter AND "device"  =~ /Unknown/ GROUP BY time($interval), "browser" fill(null)

panels.content:
Navigation Timings

What timings are important for your site?
We collect some important metrics which describe how well your site is performing.

targets.query: SELECT mean("loadEventEnd") AS "Load Event End" , mean("firstpaint") AS "First Paint", mean("responseStart") AS "Response Start" FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)

panels.content:
Ajax requests

This row shows information about your ajax calls like avg. duration.

targets.query: SELECT median(count("url")) FROM "eum_browser_ajax" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY  "url"
SELECT median(count("url")) FROM "eum_browser_ajax" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY  "url"
SELECT median(count("url")) FROM "eum_browser_ajax" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY  "url"
SELECT median(count("url")) FROM "eum_browser_ajax" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY  "url"
SELECT median(count("url")) FROM "eum_browser_ajax" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY  "url"
SELECT median(count("url")) FROM "eum_browser_ajax" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY  "url"
SELECT median(count("url")) FROM "eum_browser_ajax" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY  "url"

panels.content:
Resource requests

This row displays some informations about loaded resources.

targets.query: SELECT mean("resourceCount") FROM "eum_browser_pageload" WHERE $timeFilter

panels.content:
Resource timings

This graph shows how long the resources took to load on average.

targets.query: SELECT mean("duration") FROM "eum_browser_resourceload" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "initiatorType" fill(none)

panels.title: Average Resource Loading Time per Type
